text: Amazing. WB learned from their Doomsday trailer. Seeing it for the second time, we see Diana's sense of duty, the warrior, the compassion she feels for the world and at the start, the pain of walking away from it all. Etta Candy is funny, Steve will undoubtedly provide humour and some of the action. We see enough of Diana to know what she's like. We know Danny Huston's German officer is going to be an antagonist but we don't know WHO he is, nor what he plans to achieve, David Thewlis is still absent which means they are probably saving him for the movie. At this point Danny is either Ares/Steppenwolf and David is Zeus/Steppenwolf.   We see brighter scenes with more colour, great action and what may be the new tone of the DCEU. This is the movie to make or break the DCEU and I cannot wait to see the final trailer and then the movie itself. June 2017 cannot come sooner.

text: This looks VERY good so far, but it's hard not to feel wary after the DCEU's past output. I was cautious about Batman v Superman from the start (which was proven entirely warranted once I saw that baffling disaster), but I was genuinely excited about Suicide Squad, only to find it a frustrating, sloppy and surprisingly dull mess. And to be clear I'm not going in wanting to hate on these movies- I LOVE these characters, I LOVE the DC Universe, and I desperately WANT to like these movies, but so far they just haven't managed to get it together. I've been wanting to see a Wonder Woman movie for ages now, and I'm willing to let myself get excited for this one in spite of those recent disappointments. But for me at least this is their last chance to get me on board- if they blow it again on this one, this absolute can't-miss project that has so much going for it, I'm calling it quits on the DCEU entirely.

text: "Oh man! Did you see the Batman vs Superman trailer? Supes looking all super and shit. Batman glaring at his Batsuit and Jeremy Irons  being all like "you're consumed with rage" and shit. It's going to be AWESOME!" --- every DC fan 3 years ago.   What I'm REALLY wanting to see is WB realizing that  letting the suits edit these films into slapdash theatrical cuts compacted to fit more screenings, ISN'T a good idea. It's seriously damaged the brand.   How do you fuck up Superman and Batman first forging their legendary bond on the big screen, a bond upon which much of comic culture is BUILT in the shadow of? How do you fuck that up? With a weak script weakened even further with horrendous corporate editing and story direction that is driven by pie-chart graphs the studio put together.  Suicide Squad could have been the superhero genre's Silence of the Lambs but they played it safe and made the child murderers and domestic terrorists lovable rogues with hearts of gold when they should have been portrayed as pure evil scum who only a psycho in a Batsuit could bring down.   I want WW to destroy the global box office. She's a trinity member. She deserves the best as it's the characters first big screen outing. I just know there was lots of cool shit in those B v S and SS trailers too. The unfairly bashed Man of Steel remains the best DCEU film.

text: This is the only time when DC is ahead of Marvel - they're first in doing a proper, big budget, female superhero movie.   Considering the times we live in and how society is evolving, it couldn't be a better time for something like this. Gal Gadot is absolutely gorgeous and Patty Jenkins is a smart choice as the director.¬†   This is DC's big chance to gain the upper hand in at least one segment and to be honest - the trailer doesn't look that good. It comes off like a female version of Thor combined with Captain America: The First Avenger.   It just lacks a distinctive atmosphere and face, but maybe that's just me.  Anyway, I hope the movie delivers.¬†DC and WB¬†can't really¬†afford to fuck this up. If they do, DCU will positively remain and be remembered as the "also-ran" of this current generation of comic-book movies. Not¬†because Marvel's movies are lighter, or more family-friendly, but¬†simply because they're¬†better and because Marvel actually delivers what it sets out to deliver..

text: The war was terrible, but the Germans were not the ultimate evil the entente made her in history. While the next quote has it's fair share of propaganda, it's pointing out Germany's outlook of the war, which was silenced in the victory of the entente in 1918 and the treaty of Versailles:  In order to appreciate what Germany has accomplished during two years of war, one must to recall to mind the great" expectations which her enemies attached to this war, into which their powerful coalition for years of political scheming and thorough military preparations had enmeshed the prosperous empire at the outset, the avowed purpose of Germany's enemies  was to annihilate her,  her army, her fleet, commerce and her industry. France, hoped to regain Alsace-Lorrien, Russia hoped to conquer the provinces of east and west Prussia and Posen which were likely to recieve the "Blessings of Russian Culture" Austria-Hungary was to be dismembered, the Balkans States were to be rendered Tributary to the Czar, Constantinople and the Dardanelles were to be added to the Romanov's dominions. As for England, she deliberately entered this war because she thought she would run small risk. The world will remember the vain glorious way in which Germany's enemies foretold that before long their armies will meet at the Heart of Germany, where Cossacks were parading the streets in Berlin and Indian Lancers and Gurkhas would stroll through the parks of Potsdam, Germany would soon be Paralyzed, nay, would soon be passing away. Such were the expectations of the enemies attacking us from all sides, Germany was drawn into a war of self-defense. And today, how to Matters stand? Excepting one small corner of the empire, the only enemies on German soil are vast numbers of prisoners of war, the War is fought on enemy soil Germany and hr allies occupy 3 independent kingdoms, they hold vast areas of enemy territory, in east and west, they hold these territories firmly, without fear of losing them by force of arms. Consider the efforts our enemies made on the western front in their unsuccessful attempts at lusee and Chapmainge last autumn: suffered terrible losses and made no headway. In the spring, Germany took up the offensive against Verdun, step by step, we steadily gaining ground. The french positions are crumbling away one by one. Thanks to the genius of Hindenburg, east Germany is no longer threatened by Russians, Last year, with cooperation with our valiant ally, Austria Hungary, we drove back the Russians overwhelming their armies, for two months it is true that the Russians resumed offensive but have not succeeded in breaking through our lines. Our enemies obtain nothing but terrible losses, they achieve little but substantial gain, in no material way damaged our positions on the western front. Our enemies will probably realize in time that they are biting on Granite.... The allies have been rejoicing over the collapse of Germany, repeatedly it has been postponed Germany enters it's third year of war with unaltered confidence in in her final triumph, Germany is fighting against the greatest odds in history, she is not only fighting against the most powerful combination of enemies, but, with the world of prejudice skillful created against her." text: I've realized within the past year that Wonder Woman is actually my favorite DC superhero (I've always been more of a Marvel fan, though). I'm not sure how much this has to do with Gal Gadot playing the part (fell in love with her in Fast Five). But Superman has always been a boring superhero to me.... someone who's pretty much all-powerful and whose only weakness is a fictional glowing rock. And Batman is EVERYONE's favorite and has had more than 8 feature length films in my lifetime, so I'm kinda tired of him. I just love Wonder Woman's style of fighting and the way she kicks ass. I've also been a sucker for Greek Mythology since I was a little kid, so that adds even more to it. Plus, it's great to finally see a female superhero in a lead role of one of these blockbuster films. I'm hoping this movie will be sick as hell.

text: I know this has been said before, but screw it I'll say it myself:  I consider myself a fan of both Marvel and DC. However, I've found that Warner Bros' attempts to cash in on the success of the MCU have led to three complete messes of films due to bad writing and inconsistent editing, despite the admittedly decent cinematography and acting (most of the time). By and large, I think Marvel has been making superior movies for the past eight years with their own peaks and nadirs, but still more enjoyable to watch than the DC Extended Universe.  Batman v. Superman is a dead horse beaten to a bloody pulp already, but the fact remains that it still suffered from a dumb plot that utterly failed to capture the meaning behind the Bats/Supes fight in The Dark Knight Returns in any capacity, shoddy editing (especially in the theatrical cut, though the Ultimate Edition fixed this to an extent), weak performances by everyone who wasn't named Ben Affleck, Jeremy Irons or Gal Gadot, and a tacked on climax with Doomsday that was used FAR too early in the franchise for the Death of Superman storyline to have any kind of weight to it.  Suicide Squad, meanwhile, suffered from a plot with more holes in it than an everyday M. Night Shyamalan film, imbalanced characterization for the main characters (anyone who wasn't Deadshot, Rick Flagg, Harley Quinn, or Amanda Waller was almost completely sidelined), constant focus on probably THE worst Joker performance I've ever seen in any DC media, and the simple fact that it served no purpose than to give us that one scene at the very end where Bruce gets the files for Aquaman, Cyborg, and The Flash from Waller, which probably could have happened in a mid-credits scene in BvS if they wanted to. Oh wait, they don't do mid-credits scenes, because that would make them too similar to Marvel, AND WE CAN'T HAVE THAT NOW CAN WE!  However, this trailer has me legitimately hyped. Gadot was one of the best parts about BvS (despite her abysmal total screen time), and this trailer got me excited for her chance in the spotlight as Wonder Woman. It also seems like the writers might actually know how to treat this character, so I'm excited for that.  Overall, good trailer. Now WB, please don't screw this up again, or else I'm never going to bother with your DC movies ever again.

text: I have to say, I went into this trailer very abrasive. BVS and the first WW trailer didn't impress me, and I hadn't had my fill of seeing Gal on screen for me to be fully behind her casting. In fact, the whole DCEU as a whole has left a bad taste in my mouth (including the JL trailer).  Now, THIS TRAILER is the first where I was *squealing like an 11 year old girl seeing a dick for the first time.* XD. Seriously though, I couldn't contain my excitement when I saw the first shot of Diana on the cliff's edge seeing Steve Trevor's plane go down, I mean THE COLORS! And hearing WW proclaim her morals and beliefs about defending humankind, OH! Music to my ears! If that wasn't enough, the fanatic in me went BANANAS when I saw her blocking bullets with her bracelets,  MY GOD THE GLORY!!!  Now that I'm on this high from watching the trailer for what may be the first DCEU movie to finally do its characters justice, oh man, say it with me now:  *PLEASE DON'T SUCK. PLEASE DON'T SUCK. PLEASE DON'T SUCK.*

text: Oh please. This was in one word, pathetic. If I said this once, I've said it more times than I care to count, Lynda Carter IS Wonder Woman & Wonder Woman IS Lynda Carter. Seeing this clip doesn't do her justice. No one can fill her boots, period, end of story. This reminds me of when they tried to have Coy & Vance fill the General Lee while Bo & Luke left the Dukes Of Hazard back in the day. Granted, that was the small screen, but you get the picture. Sometimes its better off to just leave well enough alone & that was one of em much like this is another. I can also remember when they had Burt Reynolds trying too play Boss Hogg on the Dukes, Willie Nelson as Uncle Jesse, & that skank Jessica Simpson as Daisy. Are you serious? And it bombed. You CAN'T replace legends of TV like the late Sorrell Booke aka Boss Hogg, the late Denver Pyle aka Uncle Jesse, & thank God she's still with us Catherine Bach aka Daisy Duke. And the SAME can be said with Lynda Carter. Not taking anything away from the woman in this clip, but its like I said, Lynda Carter IS Wonder Woman & Wonder Woman IS Lynda Carter. It BEGINS & it ENDS right there. Bottom line, end of story. Like I said, sometimes its better off to just leave well enough alone. text: everybody keeps saying this is similar to First Avenger...the only similarity is the fact that there's a war...and it's not even the same war...First Avenger is more of an underdog story. He WANTS to join the fight, goes from Zero to Hero, loses close friend, never gives up hope etc etc and his villain is essentially his opposite.   WW is a citizen of "kick your ass" island and is completely unaware of the war, the only reason I'm guessing she wants to go is because it looks like they killed one of the other Amazon's (looks like she's not used to death for some reason)   even had they decided to go the route of using ww2 here I still think there would be enough to differentiate the stories greatly; they're really different character driven narratives.   also I feel like given the trailers introductory little blurb from her, that following the war she's gonna lose faith in humanity and possibly also be unable to return to her home island either.  really psyched for this!

text: Look, if this is yet another case of the trailer drawing us into another crappy DC Movie... I'm done with the Extended universe. I'm not going to watch Justice League Part 1, nor anything coming after it, if Wonder Woman sucks. I'm sick and tired of Zack Snyder banking on the cinematic universe reputation that Marvel garnered, but there is a reason why Marvel made it successful... They made actually universally accepted and good movies. Movies that know exactly what it wants to be, and not trying to be something it's not. After Man of Steel, Batman V Superman aka Pot vs Kettle, and Suicide Squad... I would really like an actually good movie out of DC for once. I don't go see DC, expecting it to be just like another Marvel movie. I go to see DC, to see DC films like The Dark Knight, or even the Christopher Reeves Superman Films. Back when DC did know how to make a good movie, and Marvel didn't have the Cinematic Universe to go on. So, if it turns out to be yet another polarizing movie with most people hating it, and since there will be feminists possibly defending it, people who actually like it and try to tell us you have to watch it multiple times to understand. If that's the case, then it really doesn't make sense. And how much do you want to bet that there's going to be an extended version that's only slightly better and the obligatory R rated cut? Cause Zack Snyder doesn't believe in the R rated theatrical release... Despite Deadpool being a huge success with it's R rating.

text: Why is everyone get angry about what she's wearing or lack there of? Honestly. She was raised in a strong female culture where you weren't judged for those sorts of things. The tools she uses in battle is exactly what she needs. It's a good thing that she doesn't need full body armor. No, the movie doesn't go exactly with the comics, but if you know a movie that completely lines up with the book, please let me know. YOU CAN'T EXPECT EVERY MOVIE TO BE PERFECT. Don't you dare criticize this movie solely by the 2 minute trailer and the appearance of the actress. Wonder Woman is willing to sacrifice everything she knows in order to save everyone else's butts. "Oh no, she's no Wonder Woman. She doesn't have blue eyes. Her accent is weird. She's not wearing enough clothes." Or maybe, "She's hot. I wanna hook up with her. Her legs are sexy." There are comments on this video alone worse than that. Judging a woman or anyone else based on appearances is disgusting. text: Some bits I've managed to spot and some observations:  Steve is being interrogated with the lasso of truth on him (can just barely be seen in the lower right corner of the screen).  The sword the guy is wielding near the end appears to be Diana's own sword, so she was likely disarmed at some point before that scene, and was now in the process of reacquiring it.  Certainly she has to have been on the short end of the stick at some point in the movie for proper audience anxiety and a situation to dig herself out of (78 Supes had the kryptonite necklace around his neck), and the sword being in the villains' possession hints at that.  99% certain she is not flying at the end, but has just reached the apogee of a huge jump and then the lightening may from that point contribute in suspending her  She's charging past/thru quite a bit of rapidly erupting/collapsing material before the big jump so perhaps the crossed bracers are in the process of trying to absorb the brunt of some massive energy outburst from below  Would love to see a scene in Justice League where she and the Flash are competing at bullet time reactions - he'd readily win but she would be seen to  be at a not-insignificant speed, and anyone else in the room would appear to be frozen

text: I want this movie to be a hit because , One , Gal Gadot is amazing in the role of Princess Diana/ Diana Prince /Wonder Woman  and for me the reason I said she is amazing is because her take on Diana made me forget Lynda Carter's Wonder Woman while watching BVS and these trailers, her acting has been trashed by some but if you really take the time to watch it, you can see she is one amazing face actor and does does a Really good job talking acting IMO.    Two , Both trailers for Wonder Woman  IMO show Patty Jenkins has really made a great Movie as long as the script is as good as the visual effects and attitude and no one can say this movie is too dark from the trailers.   What I find funny is people want superhero movies to be masterpieces like gone with the wind . Take these movies for what they are, movies to watch your fav hero kick butt, not make you go home in awe and amazement   BVS was no Masterpiece , the mathra part was pretty stupid but it's not gone with the wind.  Marvel is only better in they seem to avoid small dumb details like the martha but I got where that was going, they just rushed the movie and should had work the martha scene out better but for me that was the only part that was stupid, yes Wonder Woman could had killed doomsday by cutting his head off with her sword but forever reason, Superman had to die so it has to be that way and marvel movies are guilty of the same plot holes for ending a movie as above but critics seem to ignore that but I get it, one mistake vs too many mistakes. text: Did she really need a character arc based around reflecting a bullet? She has so many different backstories to choose from or draw inspiration from, but instead of leaving the island to see the glory that is the world and going from fry cook to (honorary) ambassador as she sees the best and worst of humanity, all while holding onto the ideals represented by the gifts bestowed upon her, we get invaders with guns as a 'call to adventure'. Sure, okay.  I'm entirely for a dark and dramatic storyline, but levity and pacing is needed for such stories lest you end up with Liefeld-esque narratives. In other words, all drama is depressing, but drama mixed with comedy or exciting action (requiring achievements and an overall sense of victory) is gripping and even more dramatic. To put it in another frame, if you are watching a fight, it's more gripping and heartbreaking when they both fight well then one loses/dies than it is when one guy mercilessly pounds someone much weaker.  I will say that the music in the trailer was amazing.

text: The premise of the original WW comic book was that the Nazis represented such an existential evil that all of the Amazon principles of peace and love had to be compromised to combat it. There is no such existential evil in the the WWI era. The whole international-capitalist system was responsible for the slaughter. If one had to choose the worst of the combatants, The Tsar's government was the most corrupt and repressive, followed by Wilson administration in the US. Yet she seems to be fighting on the side of the Allies. What would make more sense would be if the Amazons felt they had to conquer all of the warring powers and replace their governments with truly democratic regimes that would not fight each other.  Also, where are the elaborate bondage games on Paradise Island?

Lynda had the most innocent but beautiful face ever to grace the screen. Her costumes were made of beautiful colors and the right materials to be flattering and sexy without adding sex to the show.¬†So I will not sit through and give this movie a chance or buy into it. Instead I will continue to watch the original tv Wonder Woman on my DVD set and go back to the time when quality was much better than quantity and when lessons could be learned and super powers were used with compassion. Lynda Carter, I love you!

author: September2004

text: *SPOILERS*  Not a bad film. Certainly the best of the DCEU so far (I haven't seen Suicide Squad). Here's what I would change:  1. The Beginning needs to be better. It doesn't really get interesting until after they leave the island. It felt so cliched in the beginning with lines like, "She's a child," and, "She won't be a child forever."  2. If Steve Trevor really is British (I don't recall him indicating he was American in any way like he is in the comics) then he should have a British accent.  3. Since war is a big theme in the film, it would've been good to see her accept having to make a Sophie's Choice in war. She goes around saying, "This is wrong," a little too much in the film and it gets tired. And then, when confronted with a problem, she's able to solve it (like the trench warfare).  It would've been great if she was shown to be forced to have to make such a choice and weeps as a result. She then realizes that this is the truth of war that her mother warned her about.  4. I would've preferred she defeated Ares the same way WW defeated him in the George Perez reboot. That was so much more meaningful.  5. I don't mind Ares looking the way he does in human form, but in god form, why does he still look like that British Actor?

text: When I went to see Wonder Woman with my friend, I came out of the theatre babbling about how Diana is so strong and fierce and brave, and how she made me look forward to my next run, my next gym session, so I can work even harder and make myself stronger and faster and maybe, one day, I could be like her. I'm seventeen, and all I wanted in that moment was to *be* Wonder Woman.  When I said all this to my dad, ending with, "from now on, I'm training like Wonder Woman", he told me that what I was feeling was how he used to feel about superheroes when he was four. And how my brother felt about superheroes when he was six. I've been watching Iron Man Armoured Adventures and Justice League and reading Spiderman and Captain America comics with my brothers since I was old enough to understand the stories, and it's taken me until I'm seventeen to feel the same way they felt from the very start. Because as a girl growing up with Spiderman and Captain America and Iron Man and The Flash and Superman and Batman and Green Lantern, I never had what they had - a character I could identify with.   That's literally all it takes.

text: Finally went to see Wonder Woman in the dollar theater.  Out of ALL the reviews I read since this movie came out, not one of them‚Ä¶.NOT ONE‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ever, EVER mentioned that this is a COMEDY!  A laugh riot, farcical comedy!  OMG!!!!  I haven‚Äôt seen anything this hysterical since Liar Liar and Batman and Robin!!!    All the ‚Äúgood‚Äù reviews out there make SO much sense now!!!  The BAD acting!  The screwed up Wonder Woman storyline!  The inaccuracies GALORE!!  The laughable and incorrect ‚Äúaccents‚Äù!!!!  The FLAT CHESTED, DWARF woman playing the Amazon!  The superlative BAD, BAD casting!    OMG!  Patty Jenkins is a COMEDIC MASTER!!!  Besides the absolute brilliance at a hobbit Wonder Woman, David Thewlis as ‚ÄúAres‚Äù was divine comedy perfection!   To cast one of the best ‚ÄúC‚Äù grade actors in Britain as a ‚Äúgod‚Äù was indescribably the most brilliant comedic move to date!  I laughed so hard, I almost pee‚Äôd my pants!!  I think the ONLY actor in the whole movie who was trying to be serious, was the woman playing ‚ÄúEtta Candy‚Äù!  She was MARVELOUS!  She put everybody else to shame!  This movie isn‚Äôt billed as a comedy, so I fully expected some actual serious stuff.  But after almost cracking a few ribs after watching this enormously hysterical comedy of errors, I can see now why so many people liked it.  SUCH a good laugh!    But I have to say, DC has destroyed Wonder Woman for me.  And after being such a long time fan and collector, this just completely destroyed everything Wonder Woman stands for and fights for. text: This movie is so underrated on IMDB with only 7.6/10. I would give the movie a 5/5 in the aesthetic part because of the perfect actor choices, flawless backgrounds, fit to environment dressing and makeup.   On the theme side, comparing this movie to other superhero movies, Wonder Woman is the first female superhero movie, which is a clear example of females' rise in status in our society. It also has an anti-war theme which is rare in the action movie genre. These political-correct themes give a whole lot of meaning beyond just the movie. Thus, I would give it a 4.5/5 on the story part. 9.5/10 in total.
